        <section>
            <title>Example of building an indicator</title>
            <para>Here is an example, to show you how to build a simple indicator, to find out stock "its closing price is in 14 days highest".</para>
            <para>First, we will draft out our equation to <emphasis>Real Time Stock's Last Price >= Maximum from 14 days Stock's Last Price</emphasis></para>
            <para>
                From the equation, we know that we need to following component : 
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem><para>Real time stock information</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Relative stock history</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Equality</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Alert</para></listitem>
                </orderedlist>                         
            </para>
            <para>
                we will first add the all the components to the drawing area as below :
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="stock-indicator-editor-step1.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
                    <textobject><phrase>Stock Indicator Editor Step 1</phrase></textobject>
                </mediaobject>                  
            </para>
            
            <para>
                We will then connect all the components all together as below :
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="stock-indicator-editor-step2.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
                    <textobject><phrase>Stock Indicator Editor Step 2</phrase></textobject>
                </mediaobject>                  
            </para>            
            
            <para>
                We will need to make changes on the properties of Relative stock history and Equality, so that we can specific number of days. By right click on the 
                Relative stock history, select properties, select function=Max, type=LastPrice. Also perform right click on the Equality, select 
                properties, select equality=GreaterOrEqual. 
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="stock-indicator-editor-step3.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
                    <textobject><phrase>Stock Indicator Editor Step 3</phrase></textobject>
                </mediaobject>                  
                
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="stock-indicator-editor-step4.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
                    <textobject><phrase>Stock Indicator Editor Step 4</phrase></textobject>
                </mediaobject>                                  
            </para>  
            
            <para>
                In order to see whether we had build our indicator in correct way, we may inject in some test data. For example,
                we may check whether pbbank stock will meet this indicator criteria. Just key in pbbank in the text field, and press
                "Simulate" button. 
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="stock-indicator-editor-step5.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
                    <textobject><phrase>Stock Indicator Editor Step 5</phrase></textobject>
                </mediaobject>                                  
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="stock-indicator-editor-step6.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
                    <textobject><phrase>Stock Indicator Editor Step 6</phrase></textobject>
                </mediaobject>                 
            </para>
            
            <para>
                Once we are happy with our own built indicator, we can save it by clicking on the Save button. We are done! :)
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="stock-indicator-editor-step7.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
                    <textobject><phrase>Stock Indicator Editor Step 7</phrase></textobject>
                </mediaobject>                                                
            </para>
            
        </section>
    
